<subSubSection id="86E2D6CC244A1289B4843DB22CBB9B24" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="9AE4939A4ACBBEAAD65A9E29FFB4A64C" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="52281DDCBA9B28B0CBF43A7057C2F106" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">
The new species is most similar in leaves to 
<taxonomicName id="B748DDF9CB74983B402899473905A988" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Oreocharis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Oreocharis concava" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="concava">
<emphasis id="7B02EE340BE8E43A4576248CAA16EF58" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Oreocharis concava</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Craib) Mich. 
<normalizedToken id="13A22FB26C8A83B91370C88EAEB669B1" originalValue="MÃ¶ller">Moeller</normalizedToken>
&amp; A.Weber, but differs in broadly ovate leaf blade (
<emphasis id="10B09174B4726272D92F4A60D32F9919" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">vs.</emphasis>
oblong-ovate), remotely pubescent adaxial leaf surface (
<emphasis id="5B81273873B8A4E47FB51B288C82A30D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">vs.</emphasis>
villous), calyx margin crenate (
<emphasis id="246D2DCAF5AA0576ED33B46687C31A62" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">vs.</emphasis>
irregularly dentate), the shorter corolla (1.5-1.6 cm long 
<emphasis id="7F5109DEE1842E42C6D80C01154421CD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">vs.</emphasis>
2.2-2.8 cm), adaxial corolla lip bilobed (
<emphasis id="89911B34464DA91235844CB7A3043D7B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">vs.</emphasis>
emarginate to undivided) and disc subentire (
<emphasis id="122169084CBB585C812CFC7F84617C89" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">vs.</emphasis>
5-lobed).
</paragraph>
<caption id="93E5405D859395554F08C83CD2330789" doi="10.3897/phytokeys..32284.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/445714" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" start="Figure 7" startId="F7">
<paragraph id="EC79917CC4D24F3A1A9356757C1DDA1B" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">
<emphasis id="32FCE2D54D4856EBF3F5C818BB33B873" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Figure 7.</emphasis>
